Objectives<br>
Reflection Therapy x2 </span></TD></TR></TABLE></span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Strategy</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text>Edit: Espionage Mission should be listed with the deck (it was not with my cards when I typed the deck up), to get 42 points you must self seed THTF under Espionage and hit it with 5 people, then play Drought Tree on the complete Mission.<br>
<br>
As stated in the title, this deck revolves around the number 42 (according to the Hitchhikers Guide to the Galaxy 42 is the answer to the question of life the universe and everything). First let’s examine the seed deck. The best example of a 42-related card is Office of the President with its direct 42 shields. The Outpost with a Spacedoor has shields 24 (the reverse of 42). The Tribbles side deck has 7 cards in it (42/6=7). Otherwise, other cards are in there once each (42/42=1), to make the total cards you seed during the seed phase (including free seeds and Tribbles cards) 42.<br>
The draw deck becomes more complicated. Every card in the draw deck is in a number divisable evenly by 42 except for Drought Tree and Kivas Fajo (4 each, the first number in 42). Ships and personnel each have attributes equal to 6, 14, 21, or 24 (the first 3 divisable by 42, the latter the reverse of 42). Henc,e how Spot gets into the deck (Her Strength=0). The Drought Trees are a crucial part of the deck. All missions are 35 point planets, meaning that any completed mission+ DRought Tree=42 points.<br>
As for how to play the deck itself- Old fashioned draw cards, VCM for cards, play cards fed deck. IOAG kills this deck (Red Alert, VCM, card drawing), but as stated earlier this is purely a fun deck, meant for you to have a good time with rather than win a lot of games.  </span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="deckread.php3?deck=82"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="deckreview.php3?deck=82"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><a href="decks.php3"><img src="/stccg/global/images/back.gif" border="0" ></a></TD><TD><a href="deckprint.php3?deck=82" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="/stccg/global/images/print.gif" border="0"></a></TD></TR></TABLE> </span></td>
                      </tr>
